The United States Government takes pride in being the largest donor for global health. They are committed to various initiatives such as strengthening health systems, combating diseases like HIV/AIDS, malaria, and tuberculosis, promoting sexual and reproductive health, addressing nutrition and non-communicable diseases, and working towards universal health coverage and sustainable development. In Fiscal Year 2021, the US allocated over $9 billion for global health programs and an additional $16 billion for COVID-19 response. The Biden-Harris Administration has prioritized global health and taken steps to advance these efforts. They plan to continue their focus on global health in the coming year.